    <measure>association between imaging-based markers and stroke deterioration and recurrence</measure>
    <time_frame>two years</time_frame>
    <description>stroke caused by intracranial large artery atherosclerosis. The makers include age, gender, multiple intracranial and extracranial arterial stenosis, plaque size, severity of arterial stenosis, maximal cross-sectional area of plaques, dilated remodeling, distribution of plaques, intra-plaque hemorrhage, intra-luminal thrombus, perfusion status (ASL), quantified white matter lesions (Fazekas score &gt;2), quantified microbleeds (CMB &gt;5), and old lacunar infarcts.
stroke mainly caused by small vessel disease. The markers include age, gender, existence of intracranial plaques, existence of other large arterial disease (stenosis &gt;50%), intra-luminal thrombus, quantified white matter lesions (Fazekas score &gt;2), quantified microbleeds (CMB &gt;5), and old lacunar infarcts.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
